  "title": "Manager, Banking Operations",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Responsibilities:  </strong></u></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Operational Oversight</strong>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Oversee the accurate setup and maintenance of static data including account information, customer       profiles, pricing, and reference data.</li>\n      <li>Ensure compliance with internal controls, regulatory requirements, and audit standards.</li>\n      <li>Monitor and resolve exceptions, discrepancies, and escalations in a timely manner.</li>\n    </ul>\n  </li>\n  <li><strong>Process Improvement &amp; Risk Management</strong>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Identify opportunities to streamline processes and enhance automation.</li>\n      <li>Implement and monitor controls to mitigate operational risks.</li>\n      <li>Participate in system upgrades, UAT testing, and process re-engineering initiatives.</li>\n    </ul>\n  </li>\n  <li><strong>Reporting &amp; Governance</strong>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Prepare and present operational metrics, dashboards, and incident reports to senior management.</li>\n    </ul>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>Job Requirement</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor’s degree in Banking, Finance, Business Administration, or related field.</li>\n  <li>5+ years in banking operations</li>\n  <li>Strong attention to detail and ability to manage complex data.</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication (verbal and written) and interpersonal skills.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in MS Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint).</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of KYC and compliance procedures.</li>\n  <li>Ability to work independently and lead a team effectively.</li>\n</ul>",
